<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>21-152</num>
  <heading>Terms of sale; lien.</heading>
  <text>A sale pursuant to a decree issued pursuant to section 21-151   may be made upon such terms as to cash and credit as the court directs, and a lien shall be retained on the property sold for the purchase money.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="Pub. L. 89-183" type="History">Sept. 14, 1965, 79 Stat. 743, Pub. L. 89-183, § 1</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1973 Ed., § 21-152.</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 21-152.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
